posts.name: Brian Rozmierski
posts.cooked:
As I said in another thread:

TBA and statbotics not updating in day 2

I would encourage teams that are negatively impacted by this to, politely express to HQ how teams are using and depend on this information with an eye to allocating additional resources (if necessary) to improve reliability.

The FIRST API has been fairly reliable (outside some specific single-event cases) for several years now. I‚Äôm also not sure if FIRST HQ has a complete understanding of how widespread the useage of this data is, and how issues with it impact teams, both at home, and at an event.

posts.name: Mike O'C | 102 Scouting Mentor
posts.cooked:
I‚Äôve sent an email to FIRST replicated through a few of their customer support channels & emails (it‚Äôs not clear which support channels are more likely to be seen sooner rather than later).

I‚Äôm including it here in case anyone would like to use the verbiage as a starting point for their own communication(s) to FIRST .

Teams around the world rely on the FIRST API data for their automations and analytics. The outage currently occurring (where no schedule or match results data is available) is seriously negatively impacting the students who are depending on this service for reliable game information.

What is the current understanding of the problem? Is there anything we can collectively do to help resolve the issue? Is there an ETA on when you expect it to be resolved?

Most importantly - once this is resolved, are there changes which can be incorporated (such as updated best practices, additional resource allocations, etc.) to minimize the chances of future outages?

Hoping this works out as quickly as possible! Thanks in advance,
